photo.description: In 1583 the young Galileo Galilei (nineteen y.o.) watched the motion of the lamp that oscillated and begun to think about the law of the constant of period in the pendulum. The present lamp is of some year later, in 1587. And it's very big and heavy to easily oscillate. The one that Galileo watched was smaller, and simpler. And also lighter. It still exist today and it is inside the Aulla chapel in the near monumental cemetery.

photo.description: Pulpit - stairs from behind. The pulpit was actually disassembled and stored away during restoration work after a major fire in 1595. photo.description: Captured on Kodak Ektar 100 with Hoya 24/2.8 (Nikon FE) __________ Our last stop: Pisa and the Cathedral Square. Aside the beautiful buildings at the Square, Pisa really is a nice City, too. Would have been a pity to just visit the Piazza del Duomo. But it surely is a place worth visiting. ---------- Unser letzter Halt: Pisa und der Domplatz. Neben den wunderschönen Gebäuden am Platz, ist die Stadt Pisa auch ein sehr schöner Ort. Es wäre sehr schade gewesen nur den Piazza del Duomo zu sehen. Dennoch sollte man das nicht verpassen.
